original: Lund, Erland 15, folksk:lär. o. organist. — Mog:ex. i Halmstad 01, teol. fil. ex. i Upps. 03, teor. teol. ex. i Lund samt prästv. f. Växjö stift 06. Tj.g. som past :adj. i Tingsås o. Hin-neryd, v. pastor i Södra Hestra, Al-gutsboda, Gränna o. Visingsö, korn-min. i Gränna samt kyrkoh. i Arby-Hagby, kyrkoh. i Almundsryd sed. 30. Statsstip. i Tyskl. 22.
translated: Lund, Erland 15, elementary school teacher and organist. - Obtained a teaching degree in Halmstad in 1901, a Bachelor's degree in theology in Uppsala in 1903, and a Master's degree in theoretical theology in Lund. Was ordained as a priest in the Växjö diocese in 1906. Served as an assistant pastor in Tingsås and Hinneryd, acting pastor in Södra Hestra, Algutsboda, Gränna, and Visingsö, curate in Gränna, and parish priest in Arby-Hagby. Became the parish priest in Almundsryd since 1930. Received a government scholarship in Germany in 1922.
